# Role & Permission Guardrails

- Never trust client-side role checks alone; enforce server/rules authorization.
- Any feature that reads/writes admin collections must require staff auth.
- Any feature that changes user role/admin flags must be developer-only.
- Avoid exposing sensitive operational data to non-staff users.
- For new admin endpoints/routes, require:
  - auth token validation,
  - role check,
  - least-privilege collection access.

Before finishing, verify that UI checks and backend/rules checks agree.
